column5: Looks pretty yummy Wayne. BTW. I thought you were posting a little more than usual in the last day or so. Not hard to tell who cracks the whip at your place.
and it's not in a microwave I am impressed
Hmmm. Them eggs look kinda overcooked.  JF

So when do you actually start working 16 hours a day I assume work includes many visits to the Computer during the day and thats not for rivet diagnostics eh  Oh the fish looks so good.....................
Yep.. that kind Jed... TWO days in a row. Wonder what we should have tomorrow?

What I should have is a laptop in the shop...because I spend many hours walking back into the house and looking for pictures of stuff I've done before...so I don't reinvent the wheel. Of course I then have to check OFC...and if you notice my post count is extremely low the last couple months compared to last year Mike. I did a big stint Mike getting "santa's" airplane back to Saint Lazair. Now time to make sure everyone's float planes are fully ready for winter, as well as my fishing gear, and next is to rebuild a set of floats while I wait for a customer to get his act in gear to bring me that airplane I went and looked at the day I fished with Lew. Still don't know if I'm getting it all or part of it. If all of it... I will be going 20 hours a day if I expect to make opening day on Lake T !
Hey,,, who yanked your chain today...
So how do you survive on 4 hours sleep if you get that Wayne no wonder why you take the summer off.I guess the pepsi keeps ya fueled.
sounds like you should ship the wife off more often for these little 3 day trips.  Cheers!
Mmmmmm Captain Highliner's Haddock in the english batter.  Nice try Wayne... we all know you can't catch, let alone fillet a fish.
That photo must have been altered..... probably from a pan fulla tubesteaks!
LOL, if only it was that easy...

NO I need her back... I'm out of clean clothes..there's banking to do..bills to pay and I've got a serious itch that needs scratching.  ..and Bunk...I don't need to catch Crappie, I have a guy that just drops it off at the door (cleaned and ready to go!)
